The implementation is straightforward:

- **Line 26-27**: Declares the linker-provided symbols `__rodata_region_start` and `__rodata_region_end` as extern `char[]` arrays. These symbols are defined by the Zephyr linker script and mark the boundaries of the read-only data region.
- **Line 29-30**: Performs a range check — returns `true` if `addr` falls within `[__rodata_region_start, __rodata_region_end)`.

This matches the existing Zephyr conventions used in `soc/st/stm32/common/stm32_cache.c:49` and keeps the header self-contained (no need to include the heavy `linker-defs.h`).


